File photo:XinhuaLocal authorities in Cangxi, SW China's Sichuan have launched forensic appraisal proceedings into the death of a primary school student who was allegedly physically punished by her teacher on Thursday.    Reports say the student was beaten by her teacher with a ferule on her hands four times and punished by kneeling down on the ground for failing to answer questions. She fainted that day and was later sent to a hospital. She died on Friday.The forensic appraisal investigation is ongoing. Massive changes to California voting spark fears of Iowa-style primary chaosAsian Americans wait for their turn to shine in HollywoodCal's epidemic protection services still have room for improvement